.TH VALIDATE-INTAKE-AUTHORING-RECEIPT 1 "July 2026" "intake-authoring-governance 0.2.0"
.SH NAME
validate-intake-authoring-receipt \- validate intake source and output provenance read-only
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B validate-intake-authoring-receipt.sh
--receipt FILE [--repo PATH]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Validates backward-compatible schema-1.0 and schema-1.1 receipts and the
schema-2.0 CRUD contract. Validation covers normalized SHA-256 values, local
and public-HTTPS source evidence, clarification state, rendered command
markers, delivery authority, archived supersession evidence, and optional
series membership.
.PP
The command writes no file and grants no authoring, review, implementation, or
remote authority.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --receipt FILE
Path to the JSON receipt.
.TP
.B --repo PATH
Repository root used to resolve relative target and source paths. Defaults to
the current directory.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Print usage.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 for a current valid receipt, 2 for invalid arguments, schema violations,
source or target drift, unsafe URL evidence, missing archives, or a broken
prompt contract.
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
bash scripts/validate-intake-authoring-receipt.sh \
  --receipt specs/intake-authoring-receipts/example.json --repo .
.fi
